This paper deals with the analysis of social networks, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also uses techniques from kernel learning and spectral graph theory, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper involves discovering latent patterns in graphs, which is a problem in data science (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SY).
